SIMPLE: though
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Though
<hw>Though</hw> <pr>(⟦th⟧⟦omac⟧)</pr>, <pos>conj.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>thogh</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧ah</ets>, AS. <ets>⟦edh⟧e⟦aacute⟧h</ets>,
<ets>⟦edh⟧⟦aemac⟧h</ets>, <ets>⟦edh⟧⟦emac⟧h</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>th⟦omac⟧h</ets>, OFries. <ets>thach</ets>, D. & G. <ets>doch</ets>
but, yet, OHG. <ets>doh</ets> but, yet though, Icel.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦omac⟧</ets> yet, nevertheless, Sw. <ets>dock</ets>, Dan.
<ets>dog</ets>, Goth. <ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦aacute⟧uh</ets>,
<ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦aacute⟧u</ets>, than, or, yet; of uncertain origin.
⟦root⟧184.]</ety> <def>Granting, admitting, or supposing that;
notwithstanding that; if.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Though</qex> he slay me, yet will I trust in him.</q>
<rj><qau>Job xiii. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not that I so affirm, <qex>though</qex> so it seem.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is compounded with <xex>all</xex> in
<xex>although</xex>. See <er>Although</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>As though</b></col>, <cd>as if.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the vine were three branches; and it was <qex>as though</qex>
it budded.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xl. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Though</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Though
<hw>Though</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>However; nevertheless;
notwithstanding; -- used in familiar language, and in the middle or at
the end of a sentence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would not be as sick <qex>though</qex> for his place.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A good cause would do well, <qex>though</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thought</ent>⟦br⟧
